name: Apple Cheese Quick Bread
author: Sheila
summary: Apples, cheese and walnuts make this bread a moist and yummy treat. It tastes great with cream cheese on it!
ingredients: 2  Granny Smith apples - peeled, cored and shredded
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C)
Lightly grease a 9x5 inch loaf pan
In a large bowl, cream together the butter and sugar until light and fluffy
Beat in the honey and eggs
In a separate bowl, sift together the whole wheat flour, all-purpose flour, baking powder, soda and salt
Add the flour mixture to the butter and egg mixture; mix until combined
Fold in the apple, cheese and walnuts
Bake at 350 degrees F (175 degrees C) for 50 to 60 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted into the center of the loaf comes out clean
Turn the loaf out onto a wire rack and let cool completely
